### REST Client API Testing for Tomato Food Delivery App

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

### Get all foods
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/food

### Get food by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/food/1

### Add new food (POST) - with image upload
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/food/add
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Margherita Pizza
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Classic pizza with tomato, mozzarella, and basil
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="price"

12.99
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

pizza
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="pizza.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./uploads/pizza.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Update food
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/food/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Updated Pizza",
  "price": 13.99
}

### Delete food
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/food/1

### Create order
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/order
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "items": [
    {"foodId": 1, "quantity": 2},
    {"foodId": 2, "quantity": 1}
  ],
  "userId": "user123",
  "totalPrice": 35.97
}
